The President's statement on Cinco de Mayo highlights the victory of the Mexican people in their fight for freedom at the Battle of Puebla 151 years ago. It also celebrates the contributions and heritage of Mexican Americans and emphasizes the strong cultural, familial, and economic ties between the United States and Mexico. The President visited Mexico to further strengthen these ties and promote trade opportunities. He also stressed the importance of passing immigration reform that aligns with the nation's values and traditions. The President believes that America's diversity is its strength and encourages the celebration of the larger story of America and its unique immigrant heritage.